    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-03-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-03-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="625" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d625">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Baron <persName type="from">Fava</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Blaine</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Italy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-03-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 16,
                                1891</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Blaine</hi>: You will greatly oblige me
                            in giving me kindly the friendly assurance that, according to my private
                            note of yesterday evening, you have instructed the United States
                            legation in Rome to communicate to the royal minister of the foreign
                            office the text of your telegram to the governor of Louisiana.</p>
                <p>Many thanks for the answer.</p>
                <p>Believe me, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fava</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
